summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 21112 of the City of Seattle entitled: "An ordinance granting to the Oregon and Washington Railroad Company, its successors and assigns, the right, privilege, and authority to lay down, construct, maintain, and operate a single track railway upon and over certain lands in the City of Seattle", passed June 2, 1909; approved and filed June 14, 1909; published June 18, 1909.
